Payload.Operator: Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs

OrbitalFlights.Notes: GSAT-30 will replace INSAT-4A.
First launch contracted via the NRO's Rapid Acquisition of a Small Rocket (RASR) program.
Second OneWeb mission. Baikonur flight 1.
Satellite failed to reach orbit.

Red-Eye 2, Red-Eye 3, DeMi, and the ELaNa 30 satellite TES-10 were carried within the Cygnus spacecraft and will be released into orbit at a later date. Red-Eye 2 was deployed into orbit from ISS on 17 June 2020. Red-Eye 3 was deployed into orbit on 23 June 2020. DeMi and TechEdSat-10 were deployed on 13 July.
First Long March 2D launch from Xichang.

Final flight of Dragon 1. G-SATELLITE (Gundam Satellite) carries two miniature Gundam figurines to promote the Tokyo 2020 Summer Olympics. Quetzal-1 is Guatemala's first satellite. G-SATELLITE and Quetzal-1 were deployed into orbit from the ISS on 28 April 2020. Lynk the World, Lynk's fourth satellite, was launched to the ISS on this flight and deployed into space by the Cygnus NG-13 spacecraft on 13 May.
First flight of Long March 7A. Failed to reach orbit.
Fifth flight of booster B1048; recovery was not successful.
Baikonur flight 2.
The TDO-2 Cubesat was also known as OrCa (Orbital Calibration) by the team which designed it at Georgia Tech.
First crewed flight of Soyuz-2.1a.
Intended to replace Palapa-D. Failed to reach orbit.
First launch of the Qased.

First flight of Long March 5B, testing a new crewed spacecraft. The capsule successfully returned to Earth on 8 May, following on-orbit testing. An experimental secondary payload, meant to test inflatable heat shield reentry technologies, malfunctioned during its return to Earth on 6 May.

Xingyun-2 01/02 are the first two small satellites launched for the Xingyun narrow-band Internet of Things constellation to perform data relay and tracking services. The constellation will eventually consist of 80 such satellites.
Final HTV cargo launch, and final flight of the H-IIB rocket. The HTV-X and H3 rocket will replace them, respectively.
First orbital flight of LauncherOne. Mission was terminated shortly after first stage ignition.

Crew Dragon Demo 2: Crewed flight test of SpaceX Dragon 2 as part of the Commercial Crew Development program. Mission successfully concluded on 2 August after two months in space. First crewed orbital spaceflight with a private spacecraft.
Fifth flight of booster B1049; recovery was successful (first booster to be recovered after 5th flight).

Launch of the ELaNa 32 mission, plus additional payloads. ANDESITE will conduct magnetospheric research using an experimental fractionated formation of eight picosatellites, to be deployed after reaching orbit. Three NRO payloads were deployed as part of RASR-2.
First SmallSat Rideshare mission launch.
Last satellite of the BeiDou-3 constellation to be launched, completing the BeiDou Navigation Satellite System.
Named after African-American polar explorer Matthew Henson. Originally named Columbus.
Failed during second stage flight.
First flight of Kuaizhou 11. The rocket failed to reach space.
NROL-129 mission.
Emirates Mars Mission; first Emirati space probe.
South Korea's first dedicated military communications satellite.
China's first independent Mars mission.
It was initially planned for this Progress vehicle to deorbit the Pirs module to make way for the arrival of Nauka in early 2021. This was later delayed to a subsequent mission.
Mars 2020 mission.
Starlink SmallSat Rideshare mission to deploy BlackSky Global 7 and 8; first Starlink rideshare contracted with Spaceflight Industries, dubbed "SXRS-1".
MEV-2 successfully docked with Intelsat 10-02 on 12 April 2021.
Starlink SmallSat Rideshare mission to deploy SkySat 19–21.
First polar orbit mission from Cape Canaveral Air Force Station since ESSA-9 in 1969. SmallSat Rideshare mission to deploy Tyvak-0172 and GNOMES-1.
Return-to-flight mission for Electron. Second launch of the Photon satellite bus.

Small Satellites Mission Service Proof of Concept (SSMS PoC) mission. Return to flight for Vega after the July 2019 launch failure. 53 satellites were deployed by the SSMS dispenser, including 14 Flock CubeSats carried on SSMS QuadPack deployers, while 12 additional Flock CubeSats were deployed separately by the ION SCV LUCAS satellite. NEMO-HD and TRISAT are Slovenia's first satellites, and OSM-1 Cicero is Monaco's first satellite. Two of the Lemur-2 CubeSats failed to deploy, leading them to de-orbit along with the fourth stage of the Vega booster.
Chinese experimental reusable spaceplane.

Payload.Payload: Chongfu Shiyong Shiyan Hangtian Qi (Reusable Experimental Spacecraft)

OrbitalFlights.Notes: First flight of Rocket 3. Failed during first stage flight. Originally intended to be the second of two launches for the DARPA Launch Challenge, Rocket 3.1's launch was Astra's first orbital launch attempt following the loss of Rocket 3.0 during a prelaunch test in March 2020.

OrbitalFlights.LaunchSite: De Bo 3 Launch Platform, Yellow Sea
OrbitalFlights.Notes: Second Long March 11 sea launch.
The ELaNa 31 mission launched on this resupply flight. All CubeSats launched on this mission were successfully deployed on 5 November 2020.
Also known as GLONASS-K 705. Replaced Kosmos 2516 (GLONASS-M 753) following its failure in November 2020.
Named after the Shoshone woman Sacagawea, who helped guide the Lewis and Clark Expedition.
ÑuSat 9–18. Beihangkongshi-1 carries the first iodine electric space propulsion system to be tested in space.
First flight of Ceres-1.
The first GEM 63 solid rocket motors flew on this mission. May be an SDS satellite.
Carrying four astronauts. Second crewed and first operational Crew Dragon mission, as part of the Commercial Crew Program.
Mission failure due to human error. Cables leading to thrust vector control actuators were inverted during engine assembly, causing the AVUM upper stage to tumble upon ignition.

The DragRacer mission tested Tethers Unlimited's Terminator Tape, an electrodynamic tether that can passively de-orbit satellites in order to reduce space debris. Alchemy, the tethered satellite, was expected to take 45 days to de-orbit; Augury, the untethered satellite, was expected to take up to 9 years. Alchemy re-entered the atmosphere on 19 July 2021, after 241 days in orbit. First stage recovery using parachutes was successfully attempted on this flight, with the intact booster splashing down in the Pacific Ocean.

China's first lunar sample return mission. Lunar landing was confirmed on 1 December. The reentry capsule landed on Earth on 16 December and safely delivered 1.7 kg (3.7 lb) of lunar soil and rock samples. The orbiter is currently on an extended mission to the Sun–Earth L1 point.
First time that a Falcon 9 first-stage booster (B1049.7) has been launched and recovered for the seventh time.
Japanese Optical Data Relay Satellite.
First Long March 3B launch to sun-synchronous orbit.
First flight of the cargo version of Dragon 2. Nanoracks Bishop Airlock launched aboard this resupply flight.The airlock is now docked to the ISS as of 12/22/20.
First launch from the newly renamed Cape Canaveral Space Force Station.
Replacement for the XM-3 satellite launched in 2005. While conducting in-orbit testing the satellite experienced payload unit failures. Exact cause has not been announced.
Second orbital flight of Angara A5.
Second of three Rocket 3 orbital launch attempts. Successfully achieved an apogee of 390 km (240 mi), but fell just short of orbital velocity due to a suboptimal second stage fuel mixture.
Replacement for GSAT-12.
Vostochny flight 1. Third large batch of satellites, and the first after bankruptcy in early 2020.
NROL-108 mission.
First flight of Long March 8.
Replacement for Yaogan 33, which was lost in a launch failure on 22 May 2019.
Launch of NASA's ELaNa 20 mission. Second flight and first successful launch of LauncherOne.
First time that a Falcon 9 first stage booster (B1051) is re-flown and recovered for the 8th time and shortest turnaround for a booster so far (38 days).

Dedicated SmallSat Rideshare mission to sun-synchronous orbit, designated Transporter-1. ELaNa 35 launched aboard Spaceflight's Sherpa-FX1 as part of the SXRS-3 mission. Sherpa-FX1 hosts two on-board payloads: Celestis Horizon space burial flight and TAGSAT-1. A record 143 satellites were deployed, exceeding the previous record of 108 satellites launched by an Antares in 2018.
Second Hyperbola-1 flight. Rocket disintegrated shortly after passing max q. Contrary to initial reports, Space Ark's Fangzhou-2 (Ark-2) satellite did not launch on this flight.
Progress 77 deorbited the Pirs module to make way for the arrival of Nauka in July 2021.

At least one of the engines of the first-stage booster, B1059.6, failed during or at the end of its re-entry burn, precluding recovery of the booster. It impacted the Atlantic away from the drone ship.

The ELaNa 33 mission (consisting of one satellite, IT-SPINS) launched on this resupply flight. Carrying two undisclosed satellites. First Paraguayan and Burmese satellites launched on this flight. Tsuru, Maya-2, GuaraníSat-1, OPUSAT-II, RSP-01, WARP-01, TAU-SAT1, and STARS-EC were deployed into orbit from ISS on 14 March 2021. MMSATS-1—Myanmar's first satellite—was temporarily held on board the station, its deployment delayed due to the 2021 Myanmar coup d'état. MMSATS-1 was deployed into orbit on 22 March 2021. IT-Spins and MySat-2 were deployed into orbit on 29 June 2021 from Cygnus NG-15 after its departure from the ISS.

Payload.Operator: Kyushu Institute of Technology / Paraguayan Space Agency
Osaka Prefecture University / Muroran Institute of Technology

OrbitalFlights.Notes: First Brazilian Earth observation satellite.
Starlink V1.0-L17 mission launched after L18 and L19 due to multiple launch delays.
Reflight of the Long March 7A, which failed its maiden flight on 16 March 2020.
First time a first-stage booster flew and landed for the ninth time (B1051) and fastest turnaround time for a fairing half so far (49 days).
First fully commercial mission launched by GK Launch Services. ELSA-d will demonstrate space debris removal technology. ChallengeOne is the first Tunisian satellite.

Payload.Operator: Sapienza University of Rome / University of Nairobi / Machakos University

OrbitalFlights.Notes: Second Photon satellite. This Photon will be used to perform tests in preparation for the upcoming CAPSTONE mission.
Shiyan-6 03 is demonstrating an ultra-dark nanocomposite coating, which aims to reduce stray light interference with onboard optical sensors.
Second operational Crew Dragon mission, as part of the Commercial Crew Program.
First Long March Express commercial rideshare mission with launch services contracted by CGWIC.

Payload.Operator: Hangsheng Satellite / Zhongan Guotong Satellite Technology Development

OrbitalFlights.Notes: Small Satellites Mission Service (SSMS) piggyback mission. Return to flight for Vega after the November 2020 launch failure.
Tianhe is the core module of the Tiangong space station, providing life support and living quarters for three crew members, and guidance, navigation and attitude control for the station.
First time a first-stage booster flew and landed for the tenth time (B1051).

First of four dedicated launches for BlackSky. Second ocean splashdown recovery mission for the first stage. An anomaly occurred at second stage ignition, causing the vehicle to spin out of control. The first stage successfully splashed down using parachutes in the Pacific Ocean.
Starlink SmallSat Rideshare mission.
First Starlink orbital shell, consisting of 1,584 satellites orbiting at an altitude of 550 kilometres (340 mi), was completed with this launch.
First cargo flight to the Tiangong space station.

The ELaNa 36 mission (consisting of one satellite, RamSat) launched on this resupply flight. RamSat and SOAR were deployed into orbit from ISS on 14 June 2021. MIR-SAT1 and G-SATELLITE 2 were deployed on 22 June 2021. Two Roll Out Solar Array (iROSA) units were delivered to the station to supplement the existing ISS Solar Arrays.
Failed to reach orbit.
Tactically Responsive Launch-2 (TacRL-2) mission.
NROL-111 mission.
First crewed flight to the Tianhe core module of the Tiangong space station, with astronauts Nie Haisheng, Liu Boming and Tang Hongbo onboard.

First DoD payload to fly on the single-stick Falcon 9 with a flight-proven first stage booster; the booster B1062 previously launched GPS IIIA-04 Sacagawea in November 2020. Named after American astronaut Neil Armstrong, the first person to walk on the Moon.
Part of the Russian Liana SIGINT system.

The launch campaign is named after Tubular Bells, the first record produced by Virgin Records in 1973. STP-27VPA is composed of four military CubeSats: Gunsmoke-J 3, HALO-Net Free Flyer, and two CNCE Blk 1 satellites.

Dedicated SmallSat Rideshare mission to sun-synchronous orbit, designated Transporter-2. QMR-KWT will be Kuwait's first satellite. This launch will also carry LaserCube, Nebula and Worldfloods as hosted payloads in the ION SCV-3 deployer and TagSat-2 as hosted payload in the SHERPA-FX2 deployer. The two LINCS satellites entered an uncontrollable tumble after deployment due to "an issue with the launch vehicle".

Payload.Payload: ION Satellite Carrier 3 (ION SCV Dauntless David)

OrbitalFlights.Notes: A fairing recovery system using parachutes was tested on this launch.
Nauka was launched along with the European Robotic Arm.
Return to flight for Electron following the May 2021 launch failure, flying the Space Force's Monolith satellite as the STP-27RM mission.

Second failure in a row for the Hyperbola-1 launcher. Rocket failed to achieve correct orbit insertion after a malfunctioning in fairing separation. Jilin-1 Mofang-01A would have been the first fourth-generation Jilin-1 satellite, with a reduced payload mass of 18 kg (40 lb).
Second set of "global multimedia satellites" built by CAS for KLEO Connect.
PIRPL was deployed after NG-16 undocked from the space station.
Launch failed due to third stage ignition failure.
SSMS piggyback mission.

Third Rocket 3 orbital launch attempt and first Rocket 3 commercial flight. Vehicle also known as Rocket 3.3, which became the standard configuration used for subsequent Rocket 3 launches. STP-27AD1 consisted of equipment attached to the upper stage to verify the rocket's performance during launch. Terminated at an altitude of approximately 50 km (31 mi) due to an engine failure at liftoff, which precluded the possibility of reaching orbit.

The ELaNa 37 mission launched on this flight. Binar-1, Maya-3, Maya-4, and CUAVA-1 were deployed into orbit from the ISS on 6 October 2021. CAPSat, PR-CuNaR2, and SPACE HAUC were deployed into orbit from the ISS on 12 October 2021.

First flight of the Firefly Alpha commercial smallsat launcher. Over twenty rideshare payloads were manifested through Firefly's Dedicated Research and Education Accelerator Mission (DREAM) program. Firefly's experimental Space Utility Vehicle (SUV) was also onboard this flight. Failure occurred about two minutes after liftoff.
Replacement for ChinaSat 9A.
Operational successor to EMKA (Kosmos 2525). The identity of this military satellite is disputed; it may be EMKA №2 or Razbeg №1. Failed in orbit shortly after launch.
First launch of Starlink satellites from Vandenberg, to a 70-degree orbital inclination. First Starlink V1.5 satellites, featuring laser inter-satellite links.

Crew Dragon orbital flight carrying four civilian passengers for 3 days, led by Jared Isaacman. Mission aims to raise up to $200 million for St. Jude Children's Research Hospital by February 2022. Civilian participant Hayley Arceneaux became the first human in space with a prosthesis, and the youngest American in space.
Second cargo flight to the Tiangong space station.
Return-to-flight for Kuaizhou 1A following the September 2020 launch failure.

Satellite experienced a failure in orbit following successful launch. It was subsequently reactivated and commenced orbit raising in mid-October. The satellite reached its intended Molniya orbit in March 2022.
The ELaNa 34 mission, consisting of two CubeSats, launched on this flight. The two Cesium Mission 1 satellites experienced power failures before they could conduct their payload demonstrations.

Russian actress Yulia Peresild and filmmaker Klim Shipenko stayed on the ISS for almost 12 days and returned aboard Soyuz MS-18. Scenes for the Russian space film The Challenge were shot during their stay.

Payload.Operator: Insight Position Digital Intelligence Technology Service

OrbitalFlights.Notes: Second crewed flight to the Tiangong space station.

Maiden flight of Nuri (also known as KSLV-II), South Korea's first indigenously developed orbital launch vehicle. The third stage shut down 46 seconds prematurely, resulting in the vehicle falling short of orbital velocity. Apogee: 700 km (430 mi).
Docked to the defunct Compass-G2 (Beidou-2 G2) satellite in late December. A large orbit-raising burn was performed on 22 January 2022 to send the satellite to a high graveyard orbit.
Replacement for QZS-1 (Michibiki-1).
Launch vehicle named "Kuaizhou·Xinzhou" to commemorate the rocket assembly line in Xinzhou District, Wuhan.
Innovative Satellite Technology Demonstration-2 mission, carrying nine satellites.
Third operational Crew Dragon mission, as part of the Commercial Crew Program.
Second of four dedicated launches for BlackSky.
Fourth Rocket 3 orbital launch attempt and first to successfully reach orbit. STP-27AD2 consists of equipment attached to the upper stage to verify the rocket's performance during launch.
The Double Asteroid Redirection Test (DART) spacecraft will travel to 65803 Didymos and impact its small asteroid satellite, Dimorphos.
ISS flight 6R.
Two BlackSky satellites were launched as part of the SXRS-2 rideshare mission.
Eighth Galileo launch with Soyuz ST-B, carrying satellites Nikolina and Shriya.

Payload.Operator: Chang Guang Satellite Technology / Tianjin Yunyao Aerospace

OrbitalFlights.Notes: Space Test Program 3 (STP-3) mission. STPSat-6 hosts the Laser Communications Relay Demonstration (LCRD) payload. Ascent was deployed from LDPE-1 on 25 January 2022.
12-day mission to the ISS with a crew of three, including one professional cosmonaut and two tourists.
Third of four dedicated launches for BlackSky.
Designated SMEX-14 under NASA's Small Explorers program.

Ekspress-AMU3 and AMU7 will replace Ekspress-AM33 and Ekspress-A4, respectively. This mission could also be considered as a partial launch failure. An anomaly occurred during the firing of the Briz-M upper stage, leaving the satellites in an out-specifications orbit, so that the satellites had to do salvage maneuvers to reach their intended orbits.
First time a Falcon 9 first stage booster flew for an eleventh time.
New record for the shortest time between two SpaceX Falcon 9 launches at 15 hours and 17 minutes.

Light-1 is the first Bahraini satellite (in partnership with the UAE). The ELaNa 38 mission, consisting of four CubeSats (DAILI, GASPACS, PATCOOL, and TARGIT), launched on this flight. FEES2, GASPACS, PATCOOL, DAILI, and TARGIT were deployed into orbit from ISS on 26 January 2022. Light-1 and GT-1 were deployed on 3 February 2022.
International space observatory mission utilizing a long-wavelength visible and infrared telescope. Launching to L2.

Flight test of Persei, a Blok DM-03 upper stage variant for Angara. The upper stage failed to restart for its second planned burn, leaving itself and the dummy payload in a rapidly decaying low Earth orbit.
Iranian state media reported a successful flight, but no objects were detected in orbit following this launch. Reported apogee: 470 km (290 mi).
Dedicated SmallSat Rideshare mission to sun-synchronous orbit, designated Transporter-3.

STP-27VPB mission (ELaNa 29, GEARRS-3, and TechEdSat-3) for the Defense Innovation Unit. The ELaNa 29 mission consists of two CubeSats (PAN-A and PAN-B) that will autonomously rendezvous and dock in low Earth orbit.
First and only flight of the 511 configuration for Atlas V.
Second COSMO-SkyMed 2nd Generation satellite.

A geomagnetic storm on 4 February 2022 significantly increased atmospheric drag at the deployment altitude of these satellites, resulting in 38 of them reentering the atmosphere over the following eight days.

First launch by Astra from Cape Canaveral Space Force Station. NASA Venture Class Launch Services 2 (VCLS 2) Mission One, officially known as VCLS Demo-2A. The ELaNa 41 mission, consisting of four CubeSats, was manifested on this flight. Launch was the first approved via an FAA Part 450 launch license. An anomaly occurred around second stage ignition, resulting in a loss of mission; the failure was later found to have been caused by a wiring error in the separation mechanism and a software flaw in the thrust vector system.
The ELaNa 44 mission, consisting of one CubeSat (NACHOS), was launched on this flight. IHI-SAT and KITSUNE were deployed into orbit from the ISS on 24 March 2022.
Second Long March Express commercial rideshare mission, carrying 22 satellites.

Payload.Operator: Sanya Institute of Remote Sensing / Hainan Westar

OrbitalFlights.Notes: First of three dedicated launches for Synspective's StriX constellation. First launch from Pad B at Rocket Lab Launch Complex 1 in Mahia.
Rideshare mission.
This mission for Spaceflight, Inc. was designated Astra-1. S4 Crossover remained attached to the second stage as intended. 22 total payloads.

Maiden flight of Long March 6A, China's first rocket with solid rocket boosters. The vehicle is a further development of the Long March 6, with 2 YF-100 engines on the first stage as opposed to 1 on the Long March 6, augmented by 4 solid rocket boosters. It was also the first launch from the newly built launch complex 9A in Taiyuan.
Dedicated SmallSat Rideshare mission to sun-synchronous orbit, designated Transporter-4.
Last of four dedicated launches for BlackSky.
Axiom Mission 1, launching on Crew Dragon. Commercial flight of four (one professional and three private) astronauts to the International Space Station for a stay of 15 days.
Fourth operational Crew Dragon mission to the ISS for NASA.
Maiden flight of Angara 1.2. No orbit-raising activities were detected from Kosmos-2555 following deployment, indicating a possible spacecraft failure.

OrbitalFlights.LaunchSite: Tai Rui Launch Platform, East China Sea

OrbitalFlights.Notes: Rideshare mission. First mid-air helicopter capture attempt of an Electron first stage following launch. Copia remained attached to the kick stage as intended for a demonstration of inflatable solar arrays.
Third cargo delivery mission to the Tiangong space station.

Hyperbola-1 reflight following the launch failure on 3 August 2021, carrying a replacement for the Jilin-1 Mofang-01A satellite lost on that launch. The launch resulted in a failure, with the cause currently under investigation.
Boeing Orbital Flight Test 2 of Starliner, as part of the Commercial Crew Development program.

Dedicated SmallSat Rideshare mission to sun-synchronous orbit, designated Transporter-5. 59 small satellites and hosted payloads were launched on this mission. The Nanoracks Outpost technology demonstration mission, named Outpost Mars Demo-1 (OMD-1), will cut metal samples representative of C4M upper stages in order to test technologies for converting spent upper stages into Nanoracks Space Outposts. Sherpa-AC1 carries Xona Space's Huginn Mission and NearSpace Launch's TROOP-3 as hosted payloads, while ION SCV-006 carries Cryptosat's Crypto1 nanosatellite as a hosted payload.

Payload.Operator: Brown University School of Engineering / CNR

OrbitalFlights.Notes: First nine GeeSAT-1 satellites for the Geely Future Mobility Constellation.
Third crewed flight to the Tiangong space station. First crewed flight of the space station construction phase.
Eventual replacement for Nilesat 201, which will be decommissioned by 2028.
First of three launches for the TROPICS constellation. The second stage shut down early, resulting in a launch failure.
The identities of the secondary payloads have not been disclosed.
Second flight of Nuri, carrying a 1,500 kg (3,300 lb) dummy satellite, a 162.5 kg (358 lb) performance verification satellite and five CubeSats.
Return-to-flight for Kuaizhou 1A following the December 2021 launch failure.
MEASAT-3d will replace both MEASAT-3 and MEASAT-3a.
Launch site changed from the Mid-Atlantic Regional Spaceport to Mahia due to AFTS certification delays.
The PSLV Orbital Experimental Module (POEM), carrying 6 hosted payloads, is attached to the upper stage.
USSF-12 mission.
STP-S28A mission, carrying 7 payloads. The ELaNa 39 mission, consisting of two CubeSats, was launched on this flight.
First dedicated mission deploying Starlink satellites to sun-synchronous orbit.
NROL-162 mission.
First flight of Vega-C.
The ELaNa 45 mission, consisting of five CubeSats, was launched on this flight. TUMnanoSAT is Moldova's first satellite.
Wentian is the first Laboratory Cabin Module of the Tiangong space station, and was docked and linked to the Tianhe core module.
Maiden launch of ZK-1A. CAS Space, also known as Zhongke Aerospace, is a commercial spinoff of the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS).
Napryazhenie / 14F150 / Nivelir satellite payload.
NROL-199 mission.
Korea Pathfinder Lunar Orbiter (KPLO).
First flight of India's Small Satellite Launch Vehicle (SSLV).
TBA
Maiden flight of NASA's Space Launch System (SLS), targeting a launch period between 29 August and 5 September. 10 CubeSats will rideshare on this launch.
Second orbital launch attempt, carrying more deployable educational payloads.
First flight of RS1.
Rideshare mission.
First LauncherOne flight from Spaceport Cornwall. Oman's first satellite will launch on this flight.
First of two launches for the Space Development Agency's Tranche 0 Transport and Tracking Layer.
Fifth operational Crew Dragon mission to the ISS for NASA.
First mission of the Luna-Glob Moon exploration programme, landing near Boguslawsky crater.
Maiden flight of Jielong 3, also known as Smart Dragon 3 (SD-3).
STP-S28B mission. The ELaNa 46 mission, consisting of three CubeSats, will launch on this flight.
First GLONASS-K2 satellite.
Maiden flight of Hapith V.
First commercial smallsat mission to Mars, which will use the Exploration 3-Stage Variant of LauncherOne.
Last of three launches for the TROPICS constellation.
First Starship orbital velocity test flight, completing about three-quarters of an orbit and landing in the Pacific Ocean northwest of Kauai.
Maiden flight of Terran 1.
Maiden flight of Zhuque-2, LandSpace's first liquid-propellant rocket.
Advanced Space-based Solar Observatory (ASO-S).
Skif-D is a demonstrator satellite for the Sfera constellation.
Mengtian is the second Laboratory Cabin Module of the Tiangong space station.
Replacement for AngoSat 1, which failed shortly after launch in 2017.
Emirates Lunar Mission.
Dedicated SmallSat Rideshare mission to sun-synchronous orbit, designated Transporter-6. Vigoride-5 carries CalTech's SSPD-1 as hosted payload.
NASA Venture Class Launch Services 2 (VCLS 2) Mission Two, officially known as VCLS Demo-2FB. The ELaNa 43 mission, consisting of 11 CubeSats, will launch on this flight.
TBA
Cargo flight to the Tiangong space station. Five rideshare payloads are manifested on this flight.
Boeing Crewed Flight Test of Starliner, as part of the Commercial Crew Development program.

First Nova-C mission, which will land commercial payloads and five NASA-sponsored instruments between Mare Serenitatis and Mare Crisium for the Commercial Lunar Payload Services (CLPS) program. DOGE-1 is the first commercial lunar payload to be funded through Dogecoin.
Rideshare mission. First launch from Rocket Lab Launch Complex 2 at the Mid-Atlantic Regional Spaceport.
First OneWeb launch carried out by a Falcon 9 Block 5 rocket.

Crew Dragon orbital flight carrying four civilian passengers for 5 days, led by Jared Isaacman. Aims to conduct the first commercial spacewalk. First mission of the Polaris Program, consisting of two Crew Dragon missions followed by the first crewed Starship mission.
TBA
STP-S28C mission.
Fourth crewed flight to the Tiangong space station.
TBA
Maiden launch of Vikram 1.
Maiden flight of Vulcan Centaur.
Maiden launch of ZK-2.
First commercial launch of the Angara rocket.
Rideshare mission.
Will replace Amazonas 2.
Planned to fly with an as-yet-unnamed flight-proven Falcon 9 first-stage booster. Named after American aviation pioneer Amelia Earhart.
Replacement for IRNSS-1G.
First launch of the Orbex Prime smallsat launch vehicle.
Maiden flight of Rocket Factory Augsburg's RFA One.
Maiden flight of Rocket 4.0.
First launch of Skyrora XL.
GK Launch Services rideshare mission.
Maiden flight of Isar Aerospace's Spectrum rocket. First of two demonstration flights.
Maiden flight of the Agnibaan launch vehicle.
First flight of Blue Whale 1. Scheduled to launch after a suborbital test flight of a smaller vehicle in December 2021.
Sixth dedicated launch for BlackSky.
Orbital Test Bed (OTB) satellite carrying the Argos-4 Advanced Data Collection System (A-DCS) hosted payload.
Second of three dedicated launches for Synspective's StriX constellation.
First flight of Eris. First Australian payload to be launched into orbit on an Australian rocket.

Payload.Operator: Momentus Space / Made in Space Europe

OrbitalFlights.Notes: Will eventually replace GSAT-7.
Planned replacement for GSAT-6A.
First flight of the H3 launch vehicle.
Ocean Salinity Observation Satellite.
Multi-launch mission for Planet Labs.
As of February 2022, all Soyuz launches from Kourou have been suspended indefinitely.
First commercial SSLV launch.
NASA Venture Class Launch Services 2 (VCLS 2) Mission, officially known as VCLS Demo-2R. The ELaNa 42 mission, consisting of three CubeSats, will launch on this flight.
Rideshare mission for smallsats.
